  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. The governing requirement mandates experimental-validation as the required verification method for hemolysis QoI confirmation; however, the supporting validation activity was conducted as a high-fidelity numerical simulation benchmarked against published flow-loop data. The narrative characterises the simulation as functionally equivalent to a physical experiment given its mesh-independence and turbulence-model calibration, but the structured activityType field records 'numerical-simulation', not 'experimental-validation'. This mismatch constitutes inference-method mismatch (W-AR-03). Decision recorded as Accepted based on the persuasive narrative.",
