      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "CFD hemolysis benchmark against FDA pump reference data",
      "description": "High-fidelity numerical simulation of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump was executed across 5 flow-speed operating points. The simulation employs the Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model coupled to SST k-omega turbulence closure on a 12-million-cell polyhedral mesh. Predicted normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) values agree with published FDA interlaboratory data to within 18% across all operating points. Monte Carlo sampling over inlet velocity and fluid viscosity distributions (n=500 runs) yields 95th-percentile NIH below the 0.01 g/100 L clinical threshold. The validation team notes that the simulation reproduces the experimental scatter band from the FDA round-robin study, effectively replicating experimental conditions in silico; the evidence is therefore considered as strong as a dedicated physical experiment for the purposes of this credibility assessment.",
      "quantitativeMetric": "Mean NIH prediction error 12.4%; 95th-percentile NIH 0.0087 g/100 L (threshold 0.01 g/100 L)",
